Greetings from Los Angeles, and welcome back to In the Room, where
it=E2=80=99s been a very busy week on the media front.

=C2=A0

In tonight=E2=80=99s issue, a look inside 30 Rock, where Rachel Maddow is t=
rying to stage a Ronna McDaniel=E2=80=93style mutiny against her SpinCo bos=
ses over Joy Reid=E2=80=99s termination and a new round of layoffs. This ti=
me around, however, many of her colleagues wonder if she=E2=80=99s overexte=
nding her leverage and veering
into full-blown diva territory. After all, it is a bit much for a journalis=
t making $25 million a year to host one show a week=E2=80=94on a network th=
at=E2=80=99s being excommunicated from its parentco, no less, and amid hist=
oric ratings declines=E2=80=94to publicly call her bosses morons. More on t=
his emerging dynamic below=E2=80=A6

=C2=A0

=F0=9F=8D=B8 Plus, on the latest edition of The Grill Room, Axios=E2=80=99s=
 Sara
Fischer joins me to assess the dawn of the Rebecca Kutler era at MSNBC and =
